CSO 

  [Text] Bombay, March 2: Officers of the collectorate of 
customs, Sahar international airport, intercepted a Nigerian 
passenger departing for Accra via Addis Ababa and seized 1.30 kg 
of heroin valued at Rs 1.38 lakhs. 
  The heroin was cleverly concealed in the false bottom of a 
suitcase and was given to him for smuggling by another Nigerian. 
He was paid of Rs 12,000 and a free air ticket. 

